Internal-CA
***********

This is a CA that can be used to issue certificates for an internal PKI.


Usage
*****

The provided Makefile is used to initialise the CA, to create credentials, etc. (don't use the "./CA" script directly!)


 * "make newca"

    This deletes all issued certs and creates a new private key, effectively starting everything from scratch. 
    The subject DN of the new CA certificate is set in the Makefile. The resulting CA certificate can be found 
    in "certs/trusted/internal-unicore-cacert.pem"


 * "make servicename.pem"

    This issues a new credential for "servicename", for example "make unicorex-jupiter.pem".
    The new credential can be found in "certs/servicename.pem", in a form directly useable by UNICORE services,
    containing the (unencryted) private key, the certificate and the CA certificate key all in one pem file.
    The service's certificate can be found in "certs/servicename.cert"


 * "make all"

    This issues new credentials for the list of services preconfigured in the Makefile


 * "make list"

    This lists the DNs of all generated certificates, in the form useable for UNICORE (RFC2253)


* "make bundle"

    This creates a tgz file with all the issued credentials and certificates


Other targets like "make clean" and "make realclean" will remove generated credentials, use cautiously.